{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1527d408-720c-472c-a567-9d06dcbb3aa9","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so here's general guidance for migrating to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC):\n\n### 1. Configure NuGet.org\nOn **nuget.org → Manage Packages → Trusted Publishers**, add a new policy linking your GitHub repo, branch/tag pattern, and workflow file path.\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Before (API key):**\n```yaml\n- run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json -k ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}\n```\n\n**After (OIDC):**\n```yaml\n# Add permissions at the job level\njobs:\n  publish:\n    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n    permissions:\n      id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n      contents: read\n\n    steps:\n      - uses: actions/checkout@v4\n\n      # ... build & pack steps ...\n\n      # Install the credential provider\n      - name: Install NuGet credential provider\n        run: |\n          dotnet tool install --global NuGet.GalleryUpload ||\n          curl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/microsoft/artifacts-credprovider/master/helpers/installcredprovider.sh | bash\n\n      # Push without an API key — the OIDC token is used automatically\n      - run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg -s https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Key changes\n| What | Old | New |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Authentication** | `secrets.NUGET_API_KEY` | OIDC token (automatic) |\n| **Job permissions** | none needed | `id-token: write` |\n| **`-k` flag** | required | **remove it** |\n| **NuGet.org config** | API key in account settings | Trusted publisher policy |\n\n### 3. Clean up\n- Remove the `NUGET_API_KEY` secret from your repo/org settings once the new flow is verified.\n\nWould you like me to update a specific workflow file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"09fe0106-663a-4487-86c4-5cf4aabcca29","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the working directory. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key-based publishing to OIDC trusted publishing in GitHub Actions. Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":571,"requestId":"0FC6:E1CFB:17DD22A:1B04900:69E81A6B"},"id":"ed617f65-5327-43bc-a84d-1fabf375ae4e","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:46:47.796Z","parentId":"d45ad864-396a-41d0-a94f-d6737a5943ec"}
